{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Implemented the first real SQLAlchemy/Alembic persistence layer for the backend: explicit ORM models for sessions, workflow stage state, briefs, pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, story setup, composition/audio jobs, composition seg...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_92", "text": "Implemented the first real SQLAlchemy/Alembic persistence layer for the backend: explicit ORM models for sessions, workflow stage state, briefs, pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, story setup, composition/audio jobs, composition segments, export assets, and the event log, plus the initial migration at [20260331_01_initial_storyteller_schema.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/versions/20260331_01_initial_storyteller_schema.py). I also added shared DB base/session helpers, migration docs in [backend/README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md) and [backend/migrations/README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/README.md), and updated the architecture/domain docs to reflect the first-schema tradeoff of tracking accepted child rows on the child tables to avoid circular foreign keys.\n\nVerification passed end to end: `make check`, focused backend tests, SQLite Alembic cycle tests, and a live PostgreSQL `alembic upgrade head -> downgrade base -> upgrade head` run against the compose `postgres` service. No browser checks were needed because this prompt only changed backend persistence. The required reviewer summary is written at [11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md). Checkpoint commits: `16b904e` and `89ad342`.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 175, "prompt_index": 12, "prompt_name": "11 \u2014 PostgreSQL Schema and Database Migrations", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T22:55:18-07:00"}
